body: $ZIM They wrote this too .. "A lot of desperation and cultist posts on here. Look you bought in at 50
column4: 90 dollars and lost a packet even with those lumpy dividend payouts. I get that you are desperate to see a uptick but the fundamentals are not there. From 2012-2019 the company made an average loss of -5.7% on turnover with rates around $3300. They are now around $2700. A 30-50% payout will see a coming Div of $1- $2 and from Q2 onwards zero as there will be no profit and a price of $10-15 which is fair value. I wont read your replies"
